-- Castilla Says Peru Can Expand $4 Billion Purchase Plan
-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 2013-02-18T18:12:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-18/castilla-says-peru-can-expand-4-billion-purchase-plan.html
Peru’s government is ready to expand
a plan to purchase $4 billion of U.S. currency to support the
central bank’s effort to slow appreciation of the sol, Finance
Minister Miguel Castilla said.  The Finance Ministry will coordinate its purchases with the
central bank, which has limits to how much it can buy in the
currency market, Castilla told reporters in Lima.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in Lima at 
 jquigley8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
